Motion2D 1.3.9 is an open source release.


This file describes the changes between Motion2D 1.3.8 and 1.3.9.

****************************************************************************
*                           General                                        *
****************************************************************************

- New Open Source license: the GNU Public License (GPL) is replaced by the Q
  Public License (QPL).
- The config files are modified in order the get automatically the compiler
  version, even if GNU g++ version greater than 3.x, and addition of some
  optimization options.
- Bug fixes.

****************************************************************************
*                           Library                                        *
****************************************************************************

- In CMotion2DImage, addition of new methods: 
   . CMotion2DImage::And()

- In CMotion2DModel, addition of new methods: 
   . CMotion2DModel::invert()
   . CMotion2DModel::operator=()


****************************************************************************
*                           Examples                                        *
****************************************************************************

- The Motion2D example:
   . In the previous versions, when an error occured during the motion
     estimation the program was stopped. Now, it prints a warning like " Error
     during motion estimation, Possible reason: not enought gradient" and sets
     the estimated motion model to zero.


****************************************************************************
*                           Documentation                                  *
****************************************************************************

- Some improvements.
